    "title" : "Predictable random number based on an input string (java)",
    "body" : "<p>Given an input string, I want to generate a &quot;random&quot; number between 0 and 1.</p>\n<p>However given the same input string, the returned value should stay the same.</p>\n<p>I tried something like:</p>\n<pre><code>Random gtiRandomGenerator = new Random(input.hashCode());\nfloat gtiRandom = gtiRandomGenerator.nextFloat();\n</code></pre>\n<p>However FindBugs complained with <code>Random object created and used only once (DMI_RANDOM_USED_ONLY_ONCE)</code></p>\n",
